content.description: Climb up the arete on slopers along the lip of the vertical face. Mantle onto the slab to the top.
content.location: The right arete on the south face of the boulder.

content.description: V8? An unfinished project. Climb through tiny crimps and dishes to the lip and mantle. Ouch.
content.location: Up the tall, blank, vertical face to the right of the Call of Cthulhu crack.

content.description: Sit start low in the mini-cave on the right end of the overhang. A hard pull to an ok hold leads to jugs and an easy finish up the low-angle slab.
content.location: Sit start at the far right end of the low overhang under the tall slab.

content.description: A direct alternative the the Cultist. Begin at the undercling and sidepull and slap to the lip of the slab. Mantle with difficulty straight up to good holds. Finish up the low angle slab to the top.
content.location: Starts as for the Cultist on the low overhang beneath the tall slab.

content.description: From the undercling and sidepull slap to the slopers on the lip of the slab. Transition rightwards into ok holds then move to jugs and finish easily up the low angle slab.
content.location: Look for the short overhang below the tall, low-angle slab. Begins at a cool undercling and sidepull.

content.description: Climb the great hand crack to the top!
content.location: The obvious crack climb just left of the center of the boulder.

content.description: Start at ok edges and climb up and left to finish at the left arete at the top.
content.location: Climbs the great edges on the left end of the boulder.

content.description: Cthulhu's little sister sits just 40 feet away through the trees. The main face of the boulder is tall, very slightly overhung and quite blank. I believe the series of dime-edge crimps up the middle of the face has yet to see an ascent!
